  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "On the black sands of Isstvan V, First Captain Gabriel Santar of the Iron Hands lies broken, struck down by Julius Kaesoron of the Emperor's Children as the Dropsite Massacre claws toward its end. From the ground he watches Fulgrim — the Phoenician, his father's oldest friend — close in on Ferrus Manus, and the unblinking eyes of the Gorgon's son see what no one else has yet truly seen: the thing that wears Fulgrim's face is not, any longer, only Fulgrim. A short, intimate counterpoint to the legendary duel between primarchs, told from the dust beside it, that turns the Heresy's most famous betrayal into a moment of recognition.",
